<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>42-501</num>
  <heading>Recognized estates.</heading>
  <text>Estates in land in the District shall be estates of inheritance, estates for life, estates for years, estates at will, and estates by sufferance.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1350, ch. 854, § 1011</annotation>
    <annotation type="Cross References">Statute of frauds, see §§ <cite path="§28-3501">28-3501</cite>, <cite path="§28-3503">28-3503</cite>.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 45-201.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 45-801.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
